The paper discusses a system for approximate nearest neighbor search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV). The system is based on an inverted index, which is a common data structure used in IR and database (DB) systems. The paper also discusses the dynamic adjustment of the data structure, which is a common problem in data structures (DS) and machine learning (LG) systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.DB, and cs.LG.
